==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gyrate
<hw>Gy"rate</hw> <pr>(j⟦imac⟧"r⟦asl⟧t)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>gyratus</ets> made in a circular form, p. p. of
<ets>gyrare</ets>.]</ety> <def>Winding or coiled round; curved into a
circle; taking a circular course.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gyrate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Gyrate
<hw>Gy"rate</hw> <pr>(j⟦imac⟧"r⟦amac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Gyrated</conjf>
<pr>(j⟦imac⟧"r⟦asl⟧*t⟦ecr⟧d)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Gyrating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>gyratus</ets>, p. p. of
<ets>gyrare</ets> to gyrate. See <er>Gyre</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety>
<def>To revolve round a central point; to move spirally about an axis,
as a tornado; to revolve.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gyration</ent>⟦br⟧
